@(46-51=c3117.46) May @wDN{An}, @wDN{Enlil} and @wDN{Enki}, who have loved @wRN{Ibbi-@wDN{Suen}} from the womb, look upon him approvingly. …… is indeed placed there; they have changed (?) their appearance. With the …… and (?) the city-gates of @wSN{Urim} opening, they cry @q[,]{“Aee!” If …… says, @q[,]{“Who is my lord?” -- You are the king to whom @wDN{Enlil} has given …… no rival!

@(52-55=c3117.52) Your heart should not fret over this, ……! For …… has avenged (?) ……; he has made its foundations firm for you. Let your heart be glad over …… and (?) its seed. As long as my lord is alive, he will exercise kingship over @wSN{Urim}.

@(56-58=c3117.56) Do not suddenly reject anything that is sent as a message (?) to my lord! Before @wDN{Utu}, I will not change my word (?).



